Stir together rémoulade ingredients in a bowl and chill, covered, 1 hour. Toss shrimp with lemon, onion, celery, bay leaves, Old Bay, and salt in a large bowl, then marinate, covered, at room temperature 15 minutes. Bring beer and vinegar to a boil in large nonreactive pot. Transfer shrimp with marinade to steamer/colander insert and steam over liquid, covered, 3 minutes. Stir shrimp, then continue to steam, stirring again if necessary, until just cooked through, 3 to 5 minutes more. Transfer shrimp to a platter and drizzle with about 1/2 cup steaming liquid. Serve with rémoulade.